        <!-- ===== CAPTION ===== -->
        <mxCell id="caption" value="&lt;b&gt;Caption.&lt;/b&gt; Real demonstrations (WSD4FESDRM, §3.5) calibrate the 3CC-r muscle-fatigue ODEs (Path G) and train MMICRL (§4), which outputs per-worker safety thresholds Θ_max(z). In the env loop (Loop 1), each worker observes x_i=[MR,MA,MF]; a central NSWF planner assigns tasks j*(i) (§6, Eq.33); load-translation (§7.1) converts j* into muscle-level target loads T_L; the decentralised actor π_θ proposes neural drive C_nom (§7.2, Eq.35); the dual-barrier ECBF-QP (§5, Eq.18+23) projects it onto the safe set C*; the 3CC-r ODEs integrate to x(t+1). NSWF log-surplus forms the reward R_t and per-muscle threshold violations form the safety cost C_t, which MAPPO-Lagrangian (Loop 2) uses to update θ under a dual-ascended λ. All four prior errors (Θ_max vs δ_max, trunk F, reward log-surplus, global-state dim) corrected in place; section refs on every box are auditable against MATHEMATICAL MODELLING.pdf." style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#FFFFFF;strokeColor=#888;fontSize=10;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacingLeft=10;spacingTop=6;spacingRight=10;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="40" y="860" width="1430" height="35" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>

      </root>
    </mxGraphModel>
  </diagram>
</mxfile>
